gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Rockets 105, Knicks 103
gameRecap.excerpt: After getting fouled on a three-point attempt, Aaron Holiday hits two of three free throws with 0.3 seconds remaining in regulation to lift the Rockets over the Knicks, 105-103. Dillon Brooks led the way for the Rockets with 23 points (12 points, 4-4 3PT FG in the fourth quarter) and five rebounds, while Jabari Smith Jr. added 20 points and seven rebounds in the victory. Jalen Brunson (27 points, seven assists) and Donte DiVincenzo (23 points, five rebounds, four assists) combined for 50 points for the Knicks in the losing effort. The Rockets snap a four-game losing streak as they improve to 24-29 on the season, while the Knicks fall to 33-21.
